# ğŸ§ Commands in your notes

1. **`~` (tilde)** â†’ Shortcut to home directory

   ```bash
   cd ~
   ```

2. **`rmdir`** â†’ Remove **empty directory only**

   ```bash
   rmdir myfolder
   ```

3. **`rm -r`** â†’ Remove directory **with content**

   ```bash
   rm -r myfolder
   ```

4. **`cd`** â†’ Change directory

   ```bash
   cd Documents
   cd ..
   cd -
   ```

5. **`cp`** â†’ Copy files/directories

   ```bash
   cp file1.txt file2.txt
   cp -r folder1/ folder2/
   ```

6. **`mv`** â†’ Move or rename files

   ```bash
   mv file.txt /home/sumit/
   mv oldname.txt newname.txt
   ```

7. **`which`** â†’ Locate command binary

   ```bash
   which ls
   # Output: /bin/ls
   ```

8. **`link`** â†’ Create a hard link

   ```bash
   link file1 file2
   ```

9. **`curl`** â†’ Transfer data from/to server (URLs)

   ```bash
   curl https://example.com
   ```

